  "response": "Classical music, as a genre, wasn't invented by a single person. Instead, it developed over time through the contributions of many composers and musicians. The Classical period, which is often considered to span from about 1750 to 1820, was heavily influenced by composers such as Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart, Ludwig van Beethoven, and Joseph Haydn. These composers, among others, helped to shape and define the characteristics of Classical music during this time.",
